01:06.172 --> 01:07.757
[engine stops]

01:30.322 --> 01:31.906
[alarm blaring]

01:31.906 --> 01:34.909
[dramatic music]

01:34.909 --> 01:38.413
♪ ♪

01:38.413 --> 01:40.624
RUSSELL: Pulse rate,
body temperature,

01:40.624 --> 01:42.917
blood pressure,
respiration rate.

01:42.917 --> 01:45.462
These are the four vital signs.

01:45.462 --> 01:46.671
They indicate the status

01:46.671 --> 01:48.548
of the body's
life‐sustaining functions

01:48.548 --> 01:51.968
and serve as a basic warning
to potential health problems

01:51.968 --> 01:55.805
should these indicators
be off standard levels.

01:55.805 --> 01:58.433
But I would argue

01:58.433 --> 01:59.851
that if we want to ascertain

01:59.851 --> 02:02.228
the true health
of our patients,

02:02.228 --> 02:04.439
then these four vital signs
are not enough

02:04.439 --> 02:08.401
because they do not
monitor pain.

02:08.401 --> 02:09.944
From pain,

02:09.944 --> 02:13.948
we can instantly determine
if a patient is suffering.

02:13.948 --> 02:15.158
And what better indicator

02:15.158 --> 02:17.869
for the status
of a patient's health

02:17.869 --> 02:20.205
than the level of their pain?

02:20.205 --> 02:22.332
Therefore, I propose to you
here today

02:22.332 --> 02:24.459
in these vaunted halls

02:24.459 --> 02:28.296
that the medical community
must make pain

02:28.296 --> 02:30.548
the fifth vital sign.

02:40.600 --> 02:44.062
FINNIX: Well, it looks better.
How's it feel?

02:44.062 --> 02:45.563
‐ It feels a lot better.

02:45.563 --> 02:48.024
‐ Good.
That's what I wanna hear.

02:48.024 --> 02:51.319
So it's been four weeks.

02:51.319 --> 02:54.656
I wanna taper you off the meds.

02:54.656 --> 02:57.659
See, starting Monday,
I want you to...

02:57.659 --> 03:00.578
take one pill a day
until the next Monday,

03:00.578 --> 03:02.247
and then we're gonna
stop altogether.

03:05.125 --> 03:07.001
‐ Oh, okay.
FINNIX: Okay?

03:07.001 --> 03:08.336
‐ Sounds good.

03:08.336 --> 03:10.839
FINNIX: And if you have
a problem, you call me.

03:10.839 --> 03:14.217
You know, like you didn't do
when you first got injured?

03:14.217 --> 03:16.553
‐ [chuckles]
Yeah. You're the boss.

03:16.553 --> 03:18.096
FINNIX: That's right.
I'm the boss.

03:20.348 --> 03:24.894
So what's the latest
with Eureka Springs?

03:24.894 --> 03:26.730
‐ Oh, we called a realtor.

03:26.730 --> 03:29.441
She's looking for a place
for us.

03:29.441 --> 03:31.067
